---
import Reading from "../layouts/Reading.astro";
import { REPO_URL, HUB_URL, VERSION } from "../config";
---

<Reading
  title="Quickstart · Vela"
  description="From an empty folder to a signed finding in five commands. Real binary, real output."
  active="docs"
>
  <header class="page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow">vela quickstart</p>
    <h1 class="page-head__title">Five commands to a signed finding.</h1>
    <p class="page-head__sub">
      Empty folder, real binary, real output. No account, no API key, no central authority.
    </p>
  </header>

  <article class="qs">

    <section class="qs__step">
      <h2 class="qs__step-title">0 · Install</h2>
      <pre class="qs__code"><code>$ git clone {REPO_URL}
$ cd vela && cargo build --release -p vela-cli
$ export PATH="$PWD/target/release:$PATH"

$ vela --version
vela {VERSION}</code></pre>
      <p class="qs__note">Rust 1.79+. ~60s build on a recent laptop.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="qs__step">
      <h2 class="qs__step-title">1 · Scaffold a frontier</h2>
      <pre class="qs__code"><code>$ vela frontier new --name "demo" --description "Quickstart demo" my-frontier.json

· frontier scaffolded frontier 'demo' at my-frontier.json
  next steps:
    1. vela finding add my-frontier.json --assertion '...' --author 'reviewer:you' --apply
    2. vela sign generate-keypair --out keys
    3. vela actor add my-frontier.json reviewer:you --pubkey "$(cat keys/public.key)"
    4. vela registry publish my-frontier.json --owner reviewer:you --key keys/private.key --locator &lt;url&gt; --to {HUB_URL}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section class="qs__step">
      <h2 class="qs__step-title">2 · Add a finding</h2>
      <pre class="qs__code"><code>$ vela finding add my-frontier.json \
    --assertion "Pericyte loss precedes cognitive decline in early Alzheimer's." \
    --author "reviewer:demo" \
    --apply

Finding proposal applied
  frontier: demo
  finding:  vf_83185611d673465b
  proposal: vpr_ee0e410e7553eab9
  status:   applied
  event:    vev_6ae700c652da33ee
  wrote:    my-frontier.json</code></pre>
      <p class="qs__note">
        Without <code>--apply</code> the finding is a pending proposal in the inbox. Reviewers
        accept proposals via <code>vela queue</code>; this flag bypasses review for solo flows.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="qs__step">
      <h2 class="qs__step-title">3 · Generate a keypair</h2>
      <pre class="qs__code"><code>$ vela sign generate-keypair --out keys

· generated keypair · keys
  public key: 88ccb43144e9e228c37566554845dcd4e1f5afd3fab3e10d23df551dcdd87041</code></pre>
      <p class="qs__note">
        Ed25519 keypair on disk at <code>keys/private.key</code> and <code>keys/public.key</code>.
        The private key never leaves your machine. Back it up; losing it means losing the
        ability to sign as you.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="qs__step">
      <h2 class="qs__step-title">4 · Register the actor and sign</h2>
      <pre class="qs__code"><code>$ vela actor add my-frontier.json reviewer:demo --pubkey "$(cat keys/public.key)"

· registered actor reviewer:demo (pubkey 88ccb43144e9e228)

$ vela sign apply my-frontier.json --private-key keys/private.key

· signed 1 findings in my-frontier.json</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section class="qs__step">
      <h2 class="qs__step-title">5 · Verify</h2>
      <pre class="qs__code"><code>$ vela sign verify my-frontier.json

  VELA · SIGN · VERIFY · MY-FRONTIER.JSON
  ····························································
  total findings:   1
  signed:           1
  unsigned:         0
  valid:            1
  invalid:          0</code></pre>
      <p class="qs__note">
        The signed finding now byte-replays identically across the Rust, Python, and
        TypeScript reducers. Anyone with the file and the public key can verify locally.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="qs__step">
      <h2 class="qs__step-title">6 · Publish (optional)</h2>
      <pre class="qs__code"><code>$ vela registry publish my-frontier.json \
    --owner reviewer:demo \
    --key keys/private.key \
    --locator https://your-host.example/my-frontier.json \
    --to {HUB_URL}</code></pre>
      <p class="qs__note">
        The hub is dumb signed transport — no allowlist, no rate limit. <code>--locator</code>
        is the public URL where you serve the frontier file; the hub stores a signed manifest
        pointing at it. Skip this step if you're staying local.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="qs__step qs__step--next">
      <h2 class="qs__step-title">Next</h2>
      <ul class="qs__next">
        <li><a class="inline-link" href="/sdk">SDK reference</a> — every command, every flag, every event type.</li>
        <li><a class="inline-link" href="/spec">Protocol spec</a> — canonical-JSON, signing scheme, reducer semantics.</li>
        <li><a class="inline-link" href="/workbench">Workbench</a> — read the live BBB Flagship frontier.</li>
        <li><a class="inline-link" href={REPO_URL} rel="noopener">github.com/vela-science/vela</a> — file an issue, send a PR.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

  </article>
</Reading>

<style>
  .qs { max-width: 56rem; margin: 0 auto; }
  .qs__step {
    margin: 0 0 var(--rhythm-block);
    padding-top: 1.4rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
  }
  .qs__step:first-of-type { border-top: 0; padding-top: 0; }
  .qs__step--next { padding-top: 1.6rem; border-top-color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 32%, transparent); }
  .qs__step-title {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
  }
  .qs__code {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    background: var(--paper-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12.5px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-1);
    overflow-x: auto;
    white-space: pre;
  }
  .qs__code code { background: transparent; border: 0; padding: 0; font: inherit; color: inherit; }
  .qs__note {
    margin: 0.85rem 0 0;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .qs__note code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.86em;
    padding: 1px 5px;
    background: var(--paper-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
    border-radius: 3px;
    color: var(--ink-0);
  }
  .qs__next {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .qs__next li {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-1);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .inline-link {
    color: var(--ink-1);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 56%, transparent);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
    transition: color 160ms var(--ease), text-decoration-color 160ms var(--ease);
  }
  .inline-link:hover {
    color: var(--gold-ink);
    text-decoration-color: var(--gold-ink);
  }
</style>
